  "text": "Following the Actor-Network Theory (ANT) concept of enrolment as adapted by [CITATION_1] for examining electronic markets, we define enrolment as getting other actors to follow or act in accordance with one's own intentions. This may be achieved by a group of actions by which an organization or group of actors 'attempts to impose and stabilize the identity of other actors' (Ranerup, 2006: 284) . Enrolment thus represents a particular type of relationshipbuilding through which stakeholders are assigned an identity -which they may of course contest or reject -and a putative role to play in a company's endeavor.",
